                  <div id="innerbodycontent" class="row nolayout"><div class="offset1 span10">
            <div id="sm-cog-elements" class="noprint"></div>
            <div class="allset-page-heading"><h1>Reference:Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 2 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇)</h1></div>
            <!-- subtitle -->
            <div id="contentSub" ><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">(Redirected from <a href="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/?title=Boya_Chinese_Lower_Intermediate_2_(%E5%8D%9A%E9%9B%85%E6%B1%89%E8%AF%AD%E5%87%86%E4%B8%AD%E7%BA%A7%E5%8A%A0%E9%80%9F%E7%AF%87)&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 2 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇)">Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 2 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇)</a>)</span></div>
            <!-- /subtitle -->
                        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00112ZL5A/ref%3das_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=allset-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399373&amp;creativeASIN=B00112ZL5A"><img class="alignright" src="https&#58;//images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/51A%2BiayjnOL._SL500_AA300_.jpg" /></a>
</p><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00112ZL5A/ref%3das_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=allset-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399373&amp;creativeASIN=B00112ZL5A">Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 2 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇) </a> by Xiaoqi Li
</p>
<blockquote><p>Boya Chinese is compiled by a group of experienced teachers who teach Chinese as second language. It is divided into four levels: elementary, pre-intermediate, intermediate and advanced. There are altogether 9 books in the set which suits the four-year college study or any short-term and long-term classes. The elementary level is in two volumes of 50 lessons for beginners and covers about 1,000 words. Finishing it will ensure the students to reach level 3 of HSK. The pre-intermediate level comprises two volumes. It suits students with 1,000-3000 vocabulary. It focuses on trainings of depiction, narration, explanation and discussion. Finishing this level, the students will pass HSK test of level 5-6. The intermediate level has two volumes and is suitable for students who have 3,000-5,000 words. The contents are vivid and include a wide selection of topics. The vocabulary has very detailed notes with carefully selected examples. This level is compatible with HSK level 7-8. The advanced level is for students who master more than 5,000 words. The advanced level has three volumes and contains about 8,000-word vocabulary and focuses on identifying synonyms, explaining common sentence patterns and difficult words. There are ample exercises and interesting readings after each lesson. Finishing this level enables the students to pass HSK level 11 tests.</p></blockquote>
<p><br />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar_Points_by_Chapter">Grammar Points by Chapter</span></h2>
<ol><li>Lesson 1
<ul><li><a href="Resultative_Complement_&quot;chu(lai)&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Resultative Complement &quot;chu(lai)&quot;">"动词 + 出来" (verb + 出来)  </a></li>
<li><a href="Adding_emphasis_with_&quot;fei....buke&quot;" title="Adding emphasis with &quot;fei....buke&quot;">"非…不可"(must, have to) </a></li>
<li>"仍然" (still)</li>
<li><a href="&quot;Never_again&quot;_with_&quot;zai_ye_bu&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Never again&quot; with &quot;zai ye bu&quot;">"再也" (never again)</a></li>
<li>"渐渐"(gradually)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 2
<ul><li>"显然"(Obviously)</li>
<li><a href="Result_complement_&quot;-qilai&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Result complement &quot;-qilai&quot;">"想起来"(think of)</a></li>
<li><a href="Saying_&quot;ever_since&quot;_with_&quot;yilai&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Saying &quot;ever since&quot; with &quot;yilai&quot;">"以来"(since)</a></li>
<li><a href="Comparing_&quot;yishi&quot;_and_&quot;yidu&quot;#.E4.B8.80.E6.97.B6_can_mean_.22a_short_while.22" title="Comparing &quot;yishi&quot; and &quot;yidu&quot;">"一时"(a short while)</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_purpose_with_&quot;weile&quot;" title="Expressing purpose with &quot;weile&quot;">"为了…而"(in order to A do B)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 3
<ul><li>"倒是"(admittedly)</li>
<li>"不是没有这个可能（双重否定）"(double negatives)</li>
<li>"以上、以下"(above, below)</li>
<li>"来"(used after numbers, meaning about)</li>
<li>"趁"(while)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 4
<ul><li><a href="&quot;Never&quot;_with_&quot;conglai&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Never&quot; with &quot;conglai&quot;">"从不、从没"(never)</a></li>
<li>"哪儿…哪儿（疑问代词连用）"(using two interrogative pronouns consecutively)</li>
<li><a href="Sequencing_with_&quot;xian&quot;_and_&quot;zai&quot;" title="Sequencing with &quot;xian&quot; and &quot;zai&quot;">"先…然后（接着）"(First, then)</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;otherwise&quot;_with_&quot;yaobu&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing &quot;otherwise&quot; with &quot;yaobu&quot;">"不然（的话）"(otherwise)</a></li>
<li>"每 + 动词"(every + verb)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_Various_Aspects_with_&quot;yi_fangmian&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing Various Aspects with &quot;yi fangmian&quot;">"一方面…（另）一方面…"(on the one hand… on the other hand)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 5
<ul><li><a href="Events_in_quick_succession_with_&quot;yi..._jiu&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Events in quick succession with &quot;yi... jiu&quot;">"一 + 动词"(as soon as + verb)</a></li>
<li>"果然"(as expected)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;everyone&quot;_with_&quot;shei&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing &quot;everyone&quot; with &quot;shei&quot;">"哪儿"(everywhere)</a></li>
<li>"哪儿知道"(didn’t realize)</li>
<li><a href="Comparing_Specifically_with_&quot;xiang&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Comparing Specifically with &quot;xiang&quot;">"像…这么（那么）+ 形容词"(comparing specifically with 像)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 6
<ul><li><a href="&quot;No_Matter&quot;_with_&quot;buguan&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;No Matter&quot; with &quot;buguan&quot;">"不管…都"(not withstanding)</a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;Since&quot;_with_&quot;jiran&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Since&quot; with &quot;jiran&quot;">"既然"(since, now that)</a></li>
<li>"此外"(besides)</li>
<li>"白 + 动词"(needlessly, without cost)</li>
<li><a href="Approximating_with_sequential_numbers" title="Approximating with sequential numbers">"十二三"(approximate numbers)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 7
<ul><li>"疑问代词表任指"(using interrogative pronouns for indefinite reference)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;Even_if…&quot;_with_&quot;napa&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing &quot;Even if…&quot; with &quot;napa&quot;">"哪怕"(no matter)</a></li>
<li>"用得着/用不着"(to find something useful, to have need to)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_difficulty_with_&quot;hao_(bu)_rongyi&quot;" title="Expressing difficulty with &quot;hao (bu) rongyi&quot;">"好容易"(with great difficulty)</a></li>
<li><a href="Emphasizing_the_doer_of_an_action_with_&quot;you&quot;" title="Emphasizing the doer of an action with &quot;you&quot;">"由"(used to determine responsibility)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 8
<ul><li>"按照"(according to)</li>
<li>"当…的时候"(when)</li>
<li>"本"(oneself)</li>
<li><a href="Limiting_Scope_with_&quot;jiu&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Limiting Scope with &quot;jiu&quot;">"就"(limiting scope of a statement with 就)</a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;Along_with…&quot;_Using_&quot;suizhe&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Along with…&quot; Using &quot;suizhe&quot;">"随着"(following, along with)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 9
<ul><li><a href="Adjectival_complement_&quot;de_budeliao&quot;" title="Adjectival complement &quot;de budeliao&quot;">"不得了"(using terrible to add emphasis)</a></li>
<li>"一下子"(very quickly)</li>
<li><a href="Result_complement_&quot;xiaqu&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Result complement &quot;xiaqu&quot;">"动词/形容词 + 下去"(using 下去 to denote continuation of an action)</a></li>
<li>"恐怕"(perhaps, probably)</li>
<li>"算了"(forget it)</li>
<li><a href="Providing_two_options_with_double_&quot;huozhe&quot;" title="Providing two options with double &quot;huozhe&quot;">"或者…或者"(either…or)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 10
<ul><li><a href="Idiomatic_phrases_with_&quot;zai&quot;#Expressing_.22under.22_with_.22.E5.9C.A8....E4.B8.8B.22" title="Idiomatic phrases with &quot;zai&quot;">"在…下"(denoting conditions)</a></li>
<li>"一年（天）比一年（天）"(emphasizing change using "by the day")</li>
<li><a href="Positive_adjectives_with_&quot;-ji_le&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Positive adjectives with &quot;-ji le&quot;">"极"(extremely)</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;more_and_more&quot;_with_&quot;yue…_yue…&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing &quot;more and more&quot; with &quot;yue… yue…&quot;">"越A越B"(the more A the more B)</a></li>
<li>"引起"(lead to, to give rise to)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 11
<ul><li><a href="&quot;Within_(it/them)&quot;_as_&quot;qizhong&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Within (it/them)&quot; as &quot;qizhong&quot;">"其中"(of which)</a></li>
<li>"将"(to take) See also: <a href="Ba_sentence" class="mw-redirect" title="Ba sentence">Ba sentence</a></li>
<li>"纷纷"(in succession)</li>
<li>"则"(then, in that case)</li>
<li>"大批"(large amount, batch)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 12
<ul><li>"上（万里）"(to reach)</li>
<li><a href="Comparing_&quot;dui&quot;_and_&quot;duiyu&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;dui&quot; and &quot;duiyu&quot;">"对于"(in regard to)</a></li>
<li>"到处"(everywhere)</li>
<li>"疑问代词的虚指"(using interrogative pronouns to refer to indefinite things)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;In_the_End&quot;_with_&quot;daodi&quot;#.E5.88.B0.E5.BA.95_as_.E7.A9.B6.E7.AB.9F_or_.22on_earth.22" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing &quot;In the End&quot; with &quot;daodi&quot;">"到底"(what on earth)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 13
<ul><li><a href="&quot;One_of&quot;_with_&quot;…zhi_yi&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;One of&quot; with &quot;…zhi yi&quot;">"之一"(one of)</a></li>
<li>"然而"(however)</li>
<li>"直到、直至"(until, up to)</li>
<li><a href="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/?title=%22%E4%B8%BA(%22(verb_A_%E4%B8%BA_b)_(%E5%8D%9A%E9%9B%85%E6%B1%89%E8%AF%AD%E5%87%86%E4%B8%AD%E7%BA%A7%E5%8A%A0%E9%80%9F%E7%AF%87)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="&quot;为(&quot;(verb A 为 b) (博雅汉语准中级加速篇) (page does not exist)">"为("(verb A 为 b)</a></li>
<li>"以及"(as well as, along with)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 14
<ul><li><a href="Idiomatic_phrases_with_&quot;zai&quot;#Expressing_.22on_the_topic_of.22_with_.22.E5.9C.A8....E4.B8.8A.22" title="Idiomatic phrases with &quot;zai&quot;">"政治）上"(emphasizing a particular aspect)</a></li>
<li>"总之"(in short)</li>
<li><a href="Comparing_&quot;guanyu&quot;_and_&quot;duiyu&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;guanyu&quot; and &quot;duiyu&quot;">"关于"(with regard to)</a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;Only_if&quot;_with_&quot;zhiyou&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Only if&quot; with &quot;zhiyou&quot;">"只有…才" (only if…can)</a></li>
<li>"首先 …其次"(first…second)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 15
<ul><li>"如何"(how)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_purpose_with_&quot;weile&quot;" title="Expressing purpose with &quot;weile&quot;">"为的是"(for the purpose of)</a></li>
<li><a href="Because&quot;_with_&quot;er&quot;_Indicating_Effect" class="mw-redirect" title="Because&quot; with &quot;er&quot; Indicating Effect">"因…而"(because…so)</a></li>
<li>"从而"(thereby)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 16
<ul><li><a href="Comparing_&quot;xiande&quot;_and_&quot;kanqilai&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;xiande&quot; and &quot;kanqilai&quot;">"显得"(to appear)</a></li>
<li>"准"(most probably)</li>
<li>"意味着"(implies)</li>
<li>"动词/形容词 + 下来"(using 下来to denote a change from strong to weak)</li>
<li><a href="Using_&quot;yi...wei&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Using &quot;yi...wei&quot;">"以…为中心"(taking something to be most important)</a></li></ul></li></ol>
